1.10	Upton_Hall	Upton Hall	Upton Hall is the headquarters of the British Horological Institute (BHI) in Upton, Newark and Sherwood, Nottinghamshire, England. It has been the headquarters since 1972. It houses a library and a museum, as well as a substantial collection of antique longcase clocks, owned by the institute. The hall is open to the public all year round.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/Upton_Hall_-_geograph.org.uk_-_4563.jpg/220px-Upton_Hall_-_geograph.org.uk_-_4563.jpg
